## Task: Task shows as succeeded in web UI despite failed main workflow

cloche-98ad shows as "succeeded" in the web UI even though its main (host) workflow failed at the merge step.

## Expected
Task status should reflect that the main workflow failed. A succeeded develop step should not override a failed main workflow.

## Likely cause
Status is being derived from the develop container run (which succeeded) rather than the overall host workflow (which failed at merge). The task status should reflect the most recent attempt's worst outcome — see cloche-zupr for the planned fix to status derivation.

## Related
- cloche-zupr: Run status should reflect most recent attempt, with active statuses outweighing terminal ones
